# [DMM](../wg/dmm.html)

## Summary

The Distributed Mobility Management (DMM) Working Group met at IETF 120. The session was chaired by Satoru Matsushima (co-chair Sri Gundavelli was unable to attend). The agenda focused on status updates for active working group documents, resolution of an IESG Discuss position, and several technical presentations detailing enhancements to the Mobile User Plane (MUP) architecture, Mobile Traffic Steering (MTS), and future SRv6 requirements for 5G/6G. 

## Key Discussion Points

### Working Group Status & IESG Review
* **Presenter:** Satoru Matsushima
* **Slides:** [WG Status](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-dmm-wg-status-01)
* **Discussion:**
  * Satoru updated the group on the TN-aware mobility draft, which currently has an active "Discuss" position from the Operations Area AD. The AD noted concerns that the draft presents itself as the sole mobility solution, whereas the IETF has previously published other solutions.
  * John Kaippallimalil suggested that the wording can be clarified to resolve confusion regarding the "mobility-aware" aspects.
  * Eric Klein pointed out that the document is Informational, reflecting a long-standing intent, and supported moving it forward once the new AD's concerns are addressed.
  * Regarding 3GPP coordination, John Kaippallimalil recommended against sending a formal liaison to 3GPP SA2 on slicing, as SA2 is currently focused heavily on 6G and SA5 handles slicing.

