### Architecture Discussion on SRv6 Mobile User Plane
* **Presenter:** Teppei Kamata
* **Draft:** `draft-ietf-dmm-srv6mob-arch`
* **Slides:** [architecture-discussion-on-srv6-mobile-user-plane-03](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-dmm-architecture-discussion-on-srv6-mobile-user-plane-03-00)
* **Discussion:**
  * Teppei presented revision 03 of this informational draft, which explains why SRv6 is a strong fit for MUP by transforming mobile session info into IP routing.
  * The main update in version 03 is the clarification of the SRv6 micro-segment (NEXT-C-SID flavor, RFC 9800) and its benefits (reducing encapsulation overhead, optimizing MTU impact, and improving packet efficiency for slicing, edge computing, and URLLC).
  * John Kaippallimalil suggested adding more details on how the transition from session-based $O(N^2)$ scaling to routing-based $O(N)$ scaling is achieved through the session controller.
  * Tingji Ge asked how any-to-any communication is simplified. Teppei clarified that SRv6 MUP converts session-based point-to-point state tracking into destination-based IP routing, reducing the state tracking requirement.
* **Session Poll:**
  * **Question:** do you read this draft(architecture discussion of srv6mup)?
  * **Result:** yes: 7, no: 3, no_opinion: 0 (total: 29)

